{"title":"Feedback Sports RAKK 2.0 Holds Bigger Tires & Charges e-Bikes","link":"https://bikerumor.com/feedback-sports-rakk-2/","date":1720617713000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-0-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"feedback sports rakk 2 bike display stand.\" /></p>\n<p>The spring-loaded Feedback Sports RAKK 2.0 updates the original with the ability to hold wider tires, heavier bikes, and help manage your e-bike charging cables.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s available in two versions, the RAKK 2.0 ($60) and the RAKK 2.0 E, the latter simply adding a spot to secure the charging brick and keep your cables organized.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1.jpg\"><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1.jpg\" alt=\"feedback sports rakk 2 bike display stand.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-e-bike-storage-rack-1-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Upgrade to an e-bike in the future and you can simply add the E-Tray kit to the RAKK 2.0 later.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Otherwise, both share the same new platform with a wider, longer base for better stability when holding bikes up to 75 pounds (34kg). Rubber feet keep it from sliding around as you push your bike into place.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-2.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-2.jpg\" alt=\"feedback sports rakk 2 bike display stand.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-2.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The spring arm is 4″ taller, so it has better leverage over your bike and even works when holding the front wheel. Fold it down flat when not in use for compact storage.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-1.jpg\"><img width=\"1877\" height=\"1039\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-1.jpg\" alt=\"feedback sports rakk 2 bike display stand shown from various angles.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-1.jpg 1877w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-1-297x164.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-1-1536x850.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-1-120x66.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/feedback-sports-rakk-2-bike-storage-rack-1-768x425.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The pulley that cradles your tires is 1″ larger and now fits tires up to 4.5″ (prior model was 2.35″). It also works with road bike wheels and tires, down to 23mm, and tire diameters from 20″ up to 29″. The pulley can be bolted in at three different positions to accommodate all the wheel and tire sizes in that range, and an adapter is available for smaller 16-20″ wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://feedbacksports.com\" target=\"_blank\">FeedbackSports.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/feedback-sports-rakk-2/\">Feedback Sports RAKK 2.0 Holds Bigger Tires &amp; Charges e-Bikes</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"90cd9dca070a938b3c0b3b1044c4bb20a7a1cac005163cd90f8cffc805e7891b","category":"Cycling"}